subSubSection.paragraph:
Male postabdomen (
Fig. 37
): epandrium rounded, evenly sclerotized, setose. Hypandrium broad, with pair of short anterior setae; with rounded postgonite apically bearing strong marginal setae. Surstylus long, strongly tapered to narrow apex; apex arch posteromedially; setae confined mostly to posterior margin. Distiphallus tapered to narrow apex. Cercus elongate, longer than dorsal length of epandrium; apex rounded.

Female postabdomen (
Fig. 10
): tergite 6 (
Fig. 38
) with broadly bilobed anteriorly margin, slightly narrowed medially with sinuous posterior margin; posterior corners slightly prolonged with pair of long setae, more than half length of tergite; spermatheca (
Fig. 39
) with long pigmented denticles or papillae; without end apparatus.
